## 6. Component Patterns

### Buttons

```tsx
// Primary (yellow)
<Button>Save job</Button>
// ŌåÆ bg-[var(--mw-yellow-400)] text-[#2C2C2C] hover:bg-[var(--mw-yellow-500)]

// Ghost
<Button variant="ghost">Cancel</Button>
// ŌåÆ hover:bg-[var(--neutral-50)]

// Dark
<Button variant="dark">Export</Button>
// ŌåÆ bg-[var(--mw-mirage)] text-white hover:bg-[var(--mw-mirage)]/90

// Large (shop floor)
<Button size="lg">Start production</Button>
// ŌåÆ h-14 min-h-[56px]

// Disabled (M3 split)
<Button disabled>Locked</Button>
// ŌåÆ bg-[#0A0A0A]/[0.12] text-[#0A0A0A]/[0.38]
```

### Cards

Use `<Card>` variants from `@/components/ui/card`:
- `<Card variant="flat">` ŌĆö elevation-1, standard content card
- `<Card variant="elevated">` ŌĆö elevation-2, interactive/hover card
- `<Card variant="dark">` ŌĆö Mirage background, no shadow

For **module dashboard KPI rows**, use `<KpiStatCard>` from `@/components/shared/cards/KpiStatCard` (`iconSurface`: `onLight` | `onDark` | `key`, `standard` vs `compact` for dense 6-up KPI strips). For simple legacy inline-end KPIs, use `<StatCard>` (thin wrapper around `KpiStatCard`).
For dark hero KPI cards, use `<DarkAccentCard>` from `@/components/shared/cards/DarkAccentCard`.
For entity cards (people, suppliers), use `<EntityCard>` from `@/components/shared/cards/EntityCard`.

### Tables

Use `<MwDataTable>` from `@/components/shared/data/MwDataTable` for all data tables. It applies design-system header styling (12px uppercase tracking-wider), 56px row height, hover states, and alternating row backgrounds.

For financial/accounting tables, use `<FinancialTable>` from `@/components/shared/data/FinancialTable`.

### Progress

Use `<ProgressBar>` from `@/components/shared/data/ProgressBar`:
- `variant="linear"` ŌĆö standard single track
- `variant="segmented"` ŌĆö stepped progress bar

