## 8.5 Charts (Recharts) ŌĆö mandatory patterns

**Two colour strategies** (choose explicitly; add a one-line comment above the chart):

| Strategy | API | Use when |
|---|---|---|
| **0ŌĆō100 scale** | `getChartScaleColour(n)` | One numeric KPI normalised to 0ŌĆō100 (spend vs cap, margin, utilisation %). |
| **Categorical** | `MW_CHART_COLOURS[i]` | Distinct segments (suppliers, budget type, stacked series). |

Do **not** encode ŌĆ£good / bad / cautionŌĆØ with green / yellow / red in charts ŌĆö use the scale ramp and typography/labels for meaning.

**Shell (always):** `MW_AXIS_TICK`, `MW_CARTESIAN_GRID`, `ChartCard` or `Card variant="flat"` + `border-[var(--neutral-200)]`; tooltips via `ChartTooltip` + `MW_TOOLTIP_STYLE` where custom; `MW_RECHARTS_ANIMATION` on areas/lines; **`MW_RECHARTS_ANIMATION_BAR`** on `<Bar>`; **`cursor={MW_BAR_TOOLTIP_CURSOR}`** on `BarChart` `<Tooltip />`.

**Verification checklist (human or PR):**
1. No `#RRGGBB` in `fill` / `stroke` / chart `style` ŌĆö only `var(--*)` or helpers from `chart-theme.ts`.
2. Pie/donut slices use `MW_CHART_COLOURS` or scale-based `Cell` fills ŌĆö not arbitrary semantic colours.
3. Bar `Cell` colours match the same normalisation as any related table column if the metric is shared.
4. Bar charts use `MW_BAR_TOOLTIP_CURSOR` on `<Tooltip />` (no grey default band).
5. `npm run audit:charts` passes.

## 9. Motion

### Easing (CSS variables)

| Token | Curve | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `--ease-standard` | `cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0, 1.0)` | General transitions |
| `--ease-standard-decelerate` | `cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0, 1)` | Elements entering |
| `--ease-standard-accelerate` | `cubic-bezier(0.3, 0, 1, 1)` | Elements leaving |
| `--ease-emphasized` | `cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0, 1.0)` | Important transitions |
| `--ease-emphasized-decelerate` | `cubic-bezier(0.05, 0.7, 0.1, 1.0)` | Entering with emphasis |
| `--ease-emphasized-accelerate` | `cubic-bezier(0.3, 0, 0.8, 0.15)` | Leaving with emphasis |

### Duration

| Token | Value | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `--duration-short1` | 50ms | Micro-interactions |
| `--duration-short2` | 100ms | Simple state changes |
| `--duration-medium1` | 250ms | Standard transitions (default) |
| `--duration-medium2` | 350ms | Complex transitions |
| `--duration-long1` | 450ms | Page transitions |
| `--duration-long2` | 550ms | Emphasis transitions |

Default: `duration-[var(--duration-medium1)] ease-[var(--ease-standard)]`.
Enter: `ease-[var(--ease-standard-decelerate)]`.
Exit: `ease-[var(--ease-standard-accelerate)]`.

### Framer Motion Variants

Import from `@/components/shared/motion/motion-variants` ŌĆö never from `@/lib/design-system`:

| Export | Use |
|---|---|
| `staggerContainer`, `staggerItem` | Page-level stagger animations |
| `fadeVariants` | Simple opacity fades |
| `slideUpVariants` | Enter from below |
| `scaleVariants` | Scale + fade |
| `dialogVariants` | Dialog open/close |
| `sheetVariants` | Sheet slide in/out |
| `transitions` | Pre-built M3 transition configs |

For reduced-motion support, use `useReducedMotion` from `@/components/shared/motion/use-reduced-motion`.

## 10. Critical Rules

1. Sentence case everywhere (not Title Case)
2. Australian English (colour, organisation, metre, labour)
3. No gradients ŌĆö flat colours only
4. No decorative borders ŌĆö borders only for structure
5. Monochromatic icons (Lucide) ŌĆö no multi-colour icons
6. One primary action per card (one yellow button max)
7. No hover-only interactions on touch surfaces
8. Helpful empty states with illustration + CTA
9. Specific error messages ("Job MW-2024-0891 not found" not "Error occurred")
10. Cmd+K search always available
11. Short forms ŌĆö avoid full-page wizards
12. ShadCN/Radix components only ŌĆö no custom UI primitives
13. No Babylon.js in React state ŌĆö use refs and useEffect
14. Components under 400 lines ŌĆö split if larger
15. Use shared components from `@/components/shared/` ŌĆö never rebuild inline (see `.cursor/rules/shared-components.mdc`)
16. No `tw-animate-css`, no `next-themes`, no Tailwind grey/slate utilities (`text-gray-*`, `bg-slate-*`) ŌĆö use `var(--neutral-*)` tokens

